thread.title: Collision sparks Dodgers to 5-2 win over Mets in Game 2
thread.title_full: Collision sparks Dodgers to 5-2 win over Mets in Game 2

author: BILL PLUNKETT
title: Collision sparks Dodgers to 5-2 win over Mets in Game 2
text: Collision sparks Dodgers to 5-2 win over Mets in Game 2 Oct. 10, 2015 Updated 11:37 p.m. 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Chase Utley slides hard into second base and upends Mets shortstop Ruben Tejada in the seventh inning Saturday night. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Chase Utley slides hard into second and upends Mets' second baseman Ruben Tejada in the seventh inning. Utley was called safe and Tejada was injured on the play and left the game. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Chase Utley breaks up a double play - and the right leg of the Mets shortstop Ruben Tejada - in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Mets shortstop Ruben Tejada winces as medical personnel immobilize his right leg that he injured in a play at second in the seventh inning. Tejada was upended when the Dodgers' Chase Utley went sliding in hard to avoid a double play. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 As the crowd cheers, Dodgers players greet Chase Utley as he returns to the dugout after scoring on a double by Adrian Gonzalez in the seventh inning. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Chase Utley scores on a double by Adrian Gonzalez in the seventh inning against the Mets. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 As the crowd cheers, Dodgers players welcome Howie Kendrick after he scored in the seventh inning on a double by Adrian Gonzalez. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Howie Kendrick and Chase Utley celebrate after scoring in the seventh inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Mets starting pitcher Noah Syndergaard pitches in the second inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers starting pitcher Zack Greinke reacts after giving up his second home run in the second inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Justin Turner points to Andre Ethier from home plate after Turner scored on a double by Ethier in the fourth inning of Game 2 of the NLDS against the Mets at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers right fielder Andre Ethier goes up but can't get the home run hit by the Mets' Yoenis Cespedes in the second inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers starting pitcher Zack Greinke reacts after giving up a solo home run to Mets' Yoenis Cespedes in the second inning of Game 2 of the NLDS at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers right fielder Andre Ethier jumps up but can't catch a home run by the Mets Yoenis Cespedes in the second inning of Game 2 of the NLDS at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers starting pitcher Zack Greinke pitches in the first inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Mets starting pitcher Noah Syndergaard delivers a pitch in the first inning against the Dodgers. Syndergaard's fastball was reaching 110 mph. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Adrian Gonzalez reacts after striking out against Mets starting pitcher Noah Syndergaard in Game 2 of the NLDS at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers second baseman Howie Kendrick turns two on a double play in the first inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. The Mets' Curtis Granderson was out. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Mets' Yoenis Cespedes its greeted after hitting a home run in the second inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Mets left fielder Michael Conforto is greeted at the plate after hitting a home run in the second inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Corey Seager strikes out in the third inning with two on base in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers first baseman Adrian Gonzalez strikes out in the third inning with two on base in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Dodgers starting pitcher Zack Greinke delivers a pitch against the Mets in the first inning of game 2 of the NLDS at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. PAUL RODRIGUEZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Mets' Daniel Murphy gets caught trrying to steal in the third inning as Dodgers shortstop Corey Seager waits to make the tag in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Andre Ethier is tagged out in the fourth inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Mets left fielder Michael Conforto goes into the stands but can't reach a foul ball hit by the Dodgers' Yasmani Grandal in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Yasiel Puig bats in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Kenley Jansen closes out the Mets in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Justin Turner scores on a double by the Dodgers' Andre Ethier in the fourth inning in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Howie Kendrick celebrates in the Dodgers dugout after scoring in the seventh inning of Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Adrian Gonzalez celebrates after scoring in the seventh inning. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 The Dodgers' Enrique Hernandez steals second in the seventh inning as Mets shortstop Ruben Tejada can't make the tag in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 33 Former Dodger manager Tmmy Lasorda throws out the first pitch in Game 2 of the National League Division Series at Dodger Stadium on Saturday. MICHAEL GOULDING, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER
